<points>
<li>
There are two types of frameworks called Content-Management Systems (or CMSes
for short):<br />
<ol>
<li>
Such that are installed on the server (as a dynamic extension), are configured
somehow and are used to manage and customize the site.
</li>
<li>
Such that are operated on the developer's local machine, generate a final
static or partially dynamic site which is then uploaded as is to the server.
</li>
</ol>
</li>
</points>
